text: Win Zaw (; born 12 May 1982) is a Burmese politician and painter who currently serves as a House of Nationalities member of parliament for Kachin State № 7 constituency. He is a member of the National League for Democracy. == Early life and education == Win Zaw was born in Nantmon Village, Mohnyin Township, Kachin State on 12 May 1982. He graduated with B.A (Painting), PGDA-Painting from Mandalay University. He worked as a painter for his living. ==References== Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:People from Kachin State Category:Members of the House of Nationalities Category:National League for Democracy politicians Category:Burmese painters
